{"section": "3.8.2: The components of an inductive proof.", "qid": 0, "input_type": "fieldset", "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n </p>\n <p>\n  <b>\n   Theorem:\n  </b>\n  For all n \u2208\n  <b>\n   Z\n  </b>\n  <sup>\n   +\n  </sup>\n  , Q(n) is true,\n  <br/>\n  <br/>\n  where Q(n) is a statement that is parameterized by a positive integer n.\n </p>\n <p>\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div>\n <div class=\"text\">\n  In an inductive proof of the theorem, what must be proven in the base case?\n </div>\n</div>", "correct_choice_index": 1, "choices": ["Q(0) is true", "Q(1) is true", "Q(k) is true", "Q(n) is true"], "answer": "Q(1) is true", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"zb-explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n The first positive integer is\n <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n  n = 1\n </span>\n , so the base case shows that Q(n) is true for\n <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n  n = 1\n </span>\n .\n</div>\n", "images": {"instructions": "3.8.2-activity-instructions_div.png", "question": "3.8.2.0-activity-question.png", "choices": ["3.8.2.0-activity-choice-0.png", "3.8.2.0-activity-choice-1.png", "3.8.2.0-activity-choice-2.png", "3.8.2.0-activity-choice-3.png"], "explanation": "3.8.2-activity-explanation_div.png"}}